\begin{frame}{Motivation}
  \begin{itemize}
  \item Property-Based Testing (PBT) requires object generation.

  \item Select objects (uniformly?) from an infinite space $T$.

  \item If $f:S\to T$ is a function which is not surjective, then uniform selection in $S$
    does not correspond to uniformity in $T$.
    
  \item OBSERVATION:  When we select $s\in S$ then generate $f(s)\in T$ we often find that $f(s)$ is probably trivial.  
    
  \item GOAL: improve uniformity in $T$ by biasing the selection in $S$.

  \end{itemize}

\end{frame}

